==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Triquadrantal
<hw>Tri`quad*ran"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>tri-</ets> + <ets>quadrantal</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Spherical
Trig.)</fld> <def>Having three quadrants; thus, a
<xex>triquadrantal</xex> triangle is one whose three sides are
quadrants, and whose three angles are consequently right
angles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Triquetral</ent>⟦br⟧
